1 - Why does Android provide AsyncTasks? Give an example where AsyncTask would be useful.
    Allow background running while making the front-end responsive to user. Application with background calculations.

2 - On what thread does onPostExecute run, and why?
    UI thread.

3 -  What method do you call to switch to a new application window in Android?
     Which one do you use to switch back to the main activity?

     startActivity(Intent i), where i = new Intent(currentActivity.this, nextActivity.this);

4 - Give 2 reasons why is it useful to create an Adapter class for a third party API.
    Easier to switch to another API without largely changing the code.